Root Institute for Wisdom Culture is a beautiful oasis of tranquility located near Bodhgaya in the north Indian state of Bihar.

Because of our vicinity to the Mahabodhi Stupa, where Lord Buddha attained enlightenment, Root Institute is a unique place for practice, contemplation and blessings. Many other sites where the Buddha meditated, taught, and resided are found throughout the local landscape, making Bodhgaya the most blessed place in the Buddhist world.

For this reason, each year during our season – October through March – we offer:

pilgrimages in this region steeped in the history and culture of Buddhism, plus

Buddhist courses and retreats
introductory
intermediate and
yoga retreats integrating Buddha Dharma.
We have a separate, secluded area suitable for individual and group retreats – our Stupa Garden of Compassion.

And travellers are most welcome to come and stay with us just to enjoy a relaxed, peaceful atmosphere to unwind and rest....read more

I began my meditation practice about 12 years ago without really knowing it.  It was when I took my first yoga class.  Back then you didn’t really do yoga for the physical aspect of the practice it was more for the spiritual connection,  and that's why I started practicing yoga.  I knew I needed a change in my life, I needed something that was going to help guide me to make some positive changes and bring some peace to my life, but I wasn’t quite sure what that looked like and thought yoga was a good place to start.  
The journey has been long but well worth it.  I recently completed my first meditation teacher training and have since cultivated a daily meditation practice that I look forward to everyday.  My practice helps to keep me grounded, centered and connected to my inner peace and I want to share that with you.  
~Namaste

Eric Lindstrom is a certified practitioner through SHA, a professional chef, a permaculturist and professional multi-instrumental musician since 1990.  Eric holds a B.A. in Anthropology with a focus on The Power of Sound and Cultural Healing Practices from the University of Georgia. Eric has taught music lessons and led workshops over the years to individuals and groups. 
He feels deeply influenced and guided to the sound healing path by the vibrations and cultural immersion of his childhood time in Thailand, Bhutan, Nepal, Tibet and India.
